$interpreted: : Earlier...
Yonghyeon: Are you alright today? Did those guards give you any trouble?
Soohyeon: Don't worry about me, they're just doing their jobs.
Yonghyeon: ...Alright, then.
Soohyeon: I'm doing fine here, Yonghyeon. You don't need to come check on me every day.
Yonghyeon: ...I'm just sick of hearing about the Insect Tribe non-stop.
Soohyeon: How's all that going?
Yonghyeon: Terribly.
Yonghyeon: That stupid Tindoiimu won by total accident, and now the Insect Tribe's got the guts to start fighting back.
Soohyeon: ...Have there been many deaths?
Yonghyeon: Duh! And once Tindoiimu is arbiter, I'm sure there'll be even more.
Soohyeon: Yonghyeon, this is a struggle that has been going on for a long, long time. You can't only blame Tindoiimu.
Yonghyeon: Why!? She's the whole reason you're locked up in here! Why defend her!?
Soohyeon: I'm not defending her, but I'm not just getting angry for the sake of it. We shouldn't abandon logic at a time like this.
Soohyeon: It's easy to funnel all your blame at one person, one thing, one group. It's too easy, then that hate turns to prosecution, to war!
Worried Soldier: I'm kind of nervous about what's gonna happen to the Alliance once the new arbiter steps in...
Apathetic Guard: Whatever, no use worrying about it. It's all a huge joke, anyway, letting some maggot be the arbiter.
Yonghyeon: See? It doesn't matter what you say, everyone else is blaming her.
Yonghyeon: We shoulda taught her a lesson while we had the chance...
Soohyeon: Yonghyeon?
Yonghyeon: ...Yeah... I shoulda thought of this ages ago!
Soohyeon: Thought of what? Yonghyeon? Yonghyeon!!
Yonghyeon: Show yourself, Tindoiimu!!
Tindoiimu: What now?
Yonghyeon: I'm here to settle this!
Tindoiimu: You have a score to settle with me, Yonghyeon? If you do, I don't remember it
Yonghyeon: Quit acting all innocent! You're the reason Soohyeon is locked up!
Tindoiimu: ……
Yonghyeon: And now, all because of you, the Insect Tribe is acting up, fighting and killing!
Tindoiimu: People died and now you're blaming me? Why!? Fate is fate, and you can't change it!
Tindoiimu: Think before you speak, Yonghyeon! Think about what you and your kind did to my people in the past!
Yonghyeon: Hmph... Don't forget that a lot of our people died, too.
Yonghyeon: You lost, now you ambush us like sore losers!
Tindoiimu: (Hmph... It's no use. The situation we're in, we can't fight head to head. We have to fight from the shadows...)
Tindoiimu: (Still, I was so focused on that good news, I didn't think about their own casualties...)
TIngko: So what!? War means death, and that's that!
Tindoiimu: Tingko!?
TIngko: Don't worry, Princess. We're ready to give everything it takes to get what we want!
Tindoiimu: (What is she saying!?)
TIngko: But you just won't give up, will you? Trying to look cool for Soohyone, huh?
Yonghyeon: I am not!!
Tingko: Always with the excuses, huh?
Yonghyeon: Shut up! Just shut up!!
Tindoiimu: Tingko, watch out!
Juan-Yun: What are you doing here?
Himawari: Going to see Tindoiimu again, hmm?
Juan-Yun: It's only proper I do, she's going to be the next arbiter.
Himawari: What about me, then? What am I supposed to do?
Juan-Yun: Eh!? Fighting!? You don't think---
Himawari: Juan-Yun!
Yonghyeon: Ugh...
Tindoiimu: Enough! I don't want to start any trouble before I'm sworn in.
Yonghyeon: If you want me gone then you'll have to kill me!
Yonghyeon: Not like it matters to you, right? You'll sell out Soohyeon, kill thousands of people... what's one more life!?
Tindoiimu: ……
Tindoiimu: Whatever. I don't want to talk about it anymore.
TIngko: Do it, Princess! He'll just be a problem down the line!
Tindoiimu: Tingko...
Juan-Yun: What's going on here?
Yonghyeon: I'm here to avenge Soohyeon!
Yonghyeon: Yagh!
Tingko: Stop!!
Juan-Yun: Princess!? Princess!?
Juan-Yun: She's... not breathing...
TIngko: What are you talking about!? Don't scare me like this, Princess! Princess!!
Yonghyeon: I-I just wanted to teach her a lesson! I didn't want to... kill her...!?
Juan-Yun: Enough, Yonghyeon, just go get the doc---yaagh!
Himawari: Juan-Yun!? What's wrong!?
Juan-Yun: Mngh, ungh... Butter... princess... our lives are... linked...
TIngko: Butter!? No... Did Tindoiimu really... No!!
Himawari: What's Butter!? What are you talking about!?
Tingko: If the princess dies, Butter will bite down on the heart of whoever it inhabits.
TIngko: And right now... it's inside of Juan-Yun.
Himawari: You monster, even in death you can't leave Juan-Yun alone!?
TIngko: What are you doing!?
Himawari: If you want her to live, then shut up.
Himawari: I won't let you hurt Juan-Yun!
Himawari: damnit!!
Himawari: Wake up! Wake up!!
Tindoiimu: ...Mngh... ungh...
Tingko: Princess!! She's alive!!
Himawari: Juan-Yun!! Juan-Yun!!
Himawari: Juan-Yun, she's alive! Please, come back to life!
Tindoiimu: Gunh... Tingko... w-what happened? I... I can't feel Butter?
Tindoiimu: ...Juan... Yun...
Ace: What in the world!?
Ace: Men! Apprehend Her Majesty's attacker!
Sun Soldier: Sir!
Ace: (This is the killer, and yet... why would he do this...)
